==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Misdeed
<hw>Mis*deed"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>misd⟦aemac⟧d</ets>. See <er>Deed</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>An
evil deed; a wicked action.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Evils which our own <qex>misdeeds</qex> have wrought.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Misconduct; misdemeanor; fault; offense;
trespass; transgression; crime.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misdeem</ent>⟦br⟧
